  "description": "Application for a Non-Material Amendment Following a Grant of Planning Permission ref: 20/01480/FUL (Redevelopment of the site comprising of the demolition of the existing buildings and erection of a part 5, part 7 storey building to provide 31 affordable residential units (Use Class C3), together with associated landscaping works) granted on 29.01.2021.\r\rAmendment sought :\ri. Layout changes to the external works at ground floor level :\r  a) Adjustment of patio wall and relocation of refuse store to plot 0.01 to avoid manholes\r  b) Pedestrian gate added to plot 0.01 patio to provide access to relocated refuse store.\r  c) Side access added to plot 0.03 (including a new pedestrian gate) to provide a secondary means of escape from the rooms to the rear of the property.\rii. The boundary wall to the Central Hill elevation to be retained as existing.\riii. Layout change to the ground floor glazing to the rear of the property to allow the provision of smoke ventilation to the common area.\riv. Ground floor windows to elevation 3 to be fully glazed to improve amenity to apartments (approved drawings show obscured panels).\rv. Canopy over fourth floor exposed walkway to be extended, improving protection to circulation space and to provide a suitable route for incoming services to the apartments.\rvi. Guarding to the flat roofs on the fifth floor and to the main roof to provide safe access for maintenance.",
